{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:20:57,183", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:20:57.183550\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement a resume and job-description analysis module that extracts skills, experiences, and performs a match score.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeJobAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description, resume):\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.resume = resume\\n        self.job_keywords = self.extract_keywords(job_description)\\n        self.resume_keywords = self.extract_keywords(resume)\\n\\n    def extract_keywords(self, text):\\n        # Convert to lowercase and remove special characters\\n        text = text.lower()\\n        text = re.sub(r'[^\\\\w\\\\s]', '', text)\\n\\n        # Split into words a...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current `extract_keywords` method treats all words equally, so it doesn’t specifically extract or distinguish skills and technologies.\\n2. There’s no explicit list of matched/missing skills or a skills breakdown in the output.\\n3. The experience analysis is placeholder – it only captures “X years” but doesn’t report the number of years or factor in specific relevant project experience.\\n4. The summary labels the combined match score as “Keyword match percentage,” which is misleading.\\n5. It would be helpful to return a detailed breakdown: keyword match percentage, experience score, skills matched/missing, and total overall score.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeJobAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description: str, resume: str):\\n        self.job_description = job_description.lower()\\n        self.resume = resume.lower()\\n        # Predefined stop words\\n        self.stop_words = set([\\n            'and', 'the', 'a', 'an', 'in', 'on', 'is', 'it', 'to', 'of',\\n            'for', 'with', 'are', 'as', 'at', 'by', 'from', 'skills', 'experience'\\n        ])\\n        # Extract raw keywords\\n        self.job_keywords = self._extract_keywords(self.job_description)\\n        self.resume_keywords = self._extract_keywords(self.resume)\\n        # Extract skills lists based on job keywords\\n        self.job_skills = set(self.job_keywords)\\n        self.resume_skills = set(self.resume_keywords)\\n\\n    def _extract_keywords(self, text: str):\\n        # Remove punctuation\\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'[^\\\\w\\\\s\\\\+]', ' ', text)\\n        tokens = cleaned.split()\\n        # Filter tokens\\n        keywords = [tok for tok in tokens\\n                    if tok not in self.stop_words and len(tok) > 1]\\n        return keywords\\n\\n    def extract_experience_years(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Finds expressions like 'X years' or 'X+ years'.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        match = re.search(r'(\\\\d+)\\\\+?\\\\s+years', self.resume)\\n        if match:\\n            return int(match.group(1))\\n        return 0\\n\\n    def calculate_keyword_match(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculates percentage of job skills found in resume.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.job_skills:\\n            return 0.0\\n        matched = self.job_skills.intersection(self.resume_skills)\\n        pct = len(matched) / len(self.job_skills) * 100\\n        return round(pct, 2), matched\\n\\n    def calculate_experience_score(self, years: int):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Assigns an experience score out of 100 based on years.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if years >= 5:\\n            return 100\\n        elif years >= 3:\\n            return 75\\n        elif years >= 1:\\n            return 50\\n        else:\\n            return 25\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_score(self, kw_pct: float, exp_score: float, w_kw=0.7, w_exp=0.3):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Combines keyword and experience scores.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        overall = w_kw * kw_pct + w_exp * exp_score\\n        return round(overall, 2)\\n\\n    def run_analysis(self):\\n        # Extract years and compute scores\\n        years = self.extract_experience_years()\\n        exp_score = self.calculate_experience_score(years)\\n        kw_pct, matched_skills = self.calculate_keyword_match()\\n        overall = self.calculate_overall_score(kw_pct, exp_score)\\n\\n        # Build result\\n        return {\\n            'overall_match_score': overall,       # Combined score (0–100)\\n            'keyword_match_pct': kw_pct,          # Skill match %\\n            'matched_skills': sorted(matched_skills),\\n            'missing_skills': sorted(self.job_skills - matched_skills),\\n            'years_of_experience': years,\\n            'experience_score': exp_score,\\n            'job_skills': sorted(self.job_skills),\\n            'resume_skills': sorted(self.resume_skills),\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_description = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Software Engineer - Python\\n    We are looking for a skilled software engineer with 5+ years of experience in Python development.\\n    Experience with Django, REST APIs, and database design is required.\\n    Must have experience with Agile development methodologies.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    resume = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    Software Engineer\\n\\n    Summary:\\n    Experienced software engineer with 7 years of experience in Python.\\n\\n    Skills:\\n    Python, Django, REST APIs, SQL, Agile\\n\\n    Experience:\\n    Software Engineer at ABC Company (2016-Present)\\n    - Developed and maintained REST APIs using Django\\n    - Designed and implemented database schemas\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    analyzer = ResumeJobAnalyzer(job_description, resume)\\n    result = analyzer.run_analysis()\\n\\n    print(\\\"Overall Match Score: {}%\\\".format(result['overall_match_score']))\\n    print(\\\"Keyword Match %: {}%\\\".format(result['keyword_match_pct']))\\n    print(\\\"Matched Skills:\\\", result['matched_skills'])\\n    print(\\\"Missing Skills:\\\", result['missing_skills'])\\n    print(\\\"Years of Experience:\\\", result['years_of_experience'])\\n    print(\\\"Experience Score:\\\", result['experience_score'])\\n    print(\\\"All Job Skills:\\\", result['job_skills'])\\n    print(\\\"Extracted Resume Skills:\\\", result['resume_skills'])\\n```\"}"}
