{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:15,718", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:15.718698\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Build a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport json\\nimport random\\n\\nclass InterviewQuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_path):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewQuestionGenerator with a job description.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_path (str): Path to the JSON file containing the job description.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description_path = job_description_path\\n        self.job_description = self._load_job_description()\\n        self.technical_keywords = self._extract_keywords(\\\"...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The `generate_follow_up_question` method’s indentation is inconsistent and may cause syntax errors.\\n2. Keyword matching splits the candidate answer into single words and misses multi-word skills (e.g., \\\"REST API\\\").\\n3. It’s better to detect keywords/skills by substring matching on the full answer text (lowercased) rather than splitting.\\n4. Improved diversity: include context of the last question (technical vs. behavioral) when generating follow-ups.\\n5. Added type hints and consistent docstring formatting.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport json\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Optional\\n\\nclass InterviewQuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_path: str):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewQuestionGenerator with a job description file.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_path (str): Path to the JSON file containing the job description.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description_path = job_description_path\\n        self.job_description = self._load_job_description()\\n        self.technical_keywords = self._extract_keywords(\\\"technical_skills\\\")\\n        self.soft_skills = self._extract_keywords(\\\"soft_skills\\\")\\n\\n    def _load_job_description(self) -> dict:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Loads the job description from the specified JSON file.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing the job description, or {} on error.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            with open(self.job_description_path, \\\"r\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as f:\\n                return json.load(f)\\n        except (FileNotFoundError, json.JSONDecodeError) as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error loading job description: {e}\\\")\\n            return {}\\n\\n    def _extract_keywords(self, key: str) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts a list of keywords (technical or soft skills) from the job description.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            key (str): The key in the job description dict (\\\"technical_skills\\\" or \\\"soft_skills\\\").\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            List[str]: The list of keywords, or empty list if unavailable.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        val = self.job_description.get(key)\\n        if isinstance(val, list):\\n            return val\\n        return []\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, num_questions: int = 3) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical interview questions based on technical skills.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            num_questions (int): Number of questions to generate.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            List[str]: Generated technical questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.technical_keywords:\\n            return [\\\"No technical skills specified in job description.\\\"]\\n\\n        template = [\\n            \\\"Explain your experience with {skill}.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a project where you used {skill}.\\\",\\n            \\\"What are the advantages and disadvantages of using {skill}?\\\",\\n            \\\"How do you troubleshoot issues related to {skill}?\\\",\\n            \\\"What best practices do you follow when working with {skill}?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        questions = []\\n        for skill in random.sample(self.technical_keywords, min(num_questions, len(self.technical_keywords))):\\n            questions.append(random.choice(template).format(skill=skill))\\n        return questions\\n\\n    def generate_behavioral_questions(self, num_questions: int = 3) -> List[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates behavioral interview questions based on soft skills.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            num_questions (int): Number of questions to generate.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            List[str]: Generated behavioral questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.soft_skills:\\n            return [\\\"No soft skills specified in job description.\\\"]\\n\\n        template = [\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you demonstrated {skill}.\\\",\\n            \\\"Describe a situation where {skill} was crucial to your success.\\\",\\n            \\\"How do you handle situations where you need to improve your {skill}?\\\",\\n            \\\"Give an example of when you had to use {skill} under pressure.\\\",\\n            \\\"How do you ensure you are effectively using {skill} daily?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        questions = []\\n        for skill in random.sample(self.soft_skills, min(num_questions, len(self.soft_skills))):\\n            questions.append(random.choice(template).format(skill=skill))\\n        return questions\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up_question(\\n        self,\\n        last_question: str,\\n        candidate_answer: str\\n    ) -> Optional[str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a follow-up question based on the last question and the candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            last_question (str): The previously asked question.\\n            candidate_answer (str): The candidate's response.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            Optional[str]: A context-aware follow-up question, or None if inputs are empty.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not last_question or not candidate_answer:\\n            return None\\n\\n        answer_text = candidate_answer.lower()\\n\\n        # Look for technical keywords in the answer\\n        for tech in self.technical_keywords:\\n            if tech.lower() in answer_text:\\n                return (\\n                    f\\\"You mentioned '{tech}' in your response. \\\"\\n                    \\\"Could you walk me through a challenging problem you solved using it?\\\"\\n                )\\n\\n        # Look for soft skills in the answer\\n        for skill in self.soft_skills:\\n            if skill.lower() in answer_text:\\n                return (\\n                    f\\\"You noted '{skill}' just now. \\\"\\n                    \\\"Can you describe a specific instance where this skill made a difference?\\\"\\n                )\\n\\n        # If no direct keyword found, decide based on the type of last question\\n        if any(kw.lower() in last_question.lower() for kw in self.technical_keywords):\\n            return \\\"That's interesting. Can you provide more technical details about how you approached that?\\\"\\n        if any(skill.lower() in last_question.lower() for skill in self.soft_skills):\\n            return \\\"Could you describe how you felt during that situation and how you managed the team dynamics?\\\"\\n\\n        # Generic follow-ups\\n        generic = [\\n            \\\"Can you provide more details about that?\\\",\\n            \\\"What were the key takeaways from that experience?\\\",\\n            \\\"How did you approach that situation?\\\",\\n            \\\"What was the outcome, and what did you learn?\\\",\\n            \\\"Why was that experience important to you?\\\"\\n        ]\\n        return random.choice(generic)\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_desc = {\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"technical_skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Django\\\", \\\"REST API\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"],\\n        \\\"soft_skills\\\": [\\\"Communication\\\", \\\"Teamwork\\\", \\\"Problem-solving\\\"]\\n    }\\n    with open(\\\"job_description.json\\\", \\\"w\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as f:\\n        json.dump(job_desc, f)\\n\\n    gen = InterviewQuestionGenerator(\\\"job_description.json\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"Tech Questions:\\\", gen.generate_technical_questions(2))\\n    print(\\\"Behavioral Questions:\\\", gen.generate_behavioral_questions(2))\\n\\n    last_q = \\\"Tell me about a time you demonstrated teamwork.\\\"\\n    answer = \\\"I worked on a project using REST API extensively, and communication was key during standups.\\\"\\n    print(\\\"Follow-up:\\\", gen.generate_follow_up_question(last_q, answer))\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:37,017", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement an evaluation engine that scores candidate answers on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy across categories.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_question, topic, depth=1):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\\n        previous_question (str): The question that elicited the response.\\n        topic (str): The general topic of the interview question.\\n        depth (int):  The desired depth/specificity of the follow-up question. Higher depth means more specific.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of follow-up questions (strings).  Returns an empty list if no follow-up questions can be generated.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    follow_up_questions = []\\n\\n    # Basic examples; can be expanded with more sophisticated logic\\n    # (e.g., using NLP to analyze the response and identify areas for further probing).\\n\\n    if depth == 1:\\n        if \\\"experience\\\" in topic.lower() or \\\"project\\\" in topic.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"Can you elaborate on a specific challenge you faced during that experience/project and how you overcame it?\\\")\\n        elif \\\"algorithm\\\" in topic.lower() or \\\"data structure\\\" in topic.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"What are the time and space complexity trade-offs of using that algorithm/data structure in this scenario?\\\")\\n        elif \\\"behavioral\\\" in topic.lower() or \\\"conflict\\\" in topic.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"What was the outcome, and what did you learn from the situation?\\\")\\n        else:\\n             follow_up_questions.append(\\\"Could you provide more details about that?\\\")\\n\\n\\n    elif depth == 2: # Requires deeper understanding of the response\\n        if \\\"challenge\\\" in candidate_response.lower() and \\\"overcame\\\" in candidate_response.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"What alternative solutions did you consider before deciding on your final approach?\\\")\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"How did you measure the success of your solution?\\\")\\n        elif \\\"time complexity\\\" in candidate_response.lower() or \\\"space complexity\\\" in candidate_response.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"How does the complexity change with different input sizes or data distributions?\\\")\\n        elif \\\"learned\\\" in candidate_response.lower():\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"How have you applied that learning in subsequent projects or situations?\\\")\\n        else:\\n            follow_up_questions.append(\\\"Can you give a concrete example to illustrate your point?\\\")\\n\\n    # Add more depth levels and condition based on keywords/concepts in candidate_response\\n    # using NLP techniques for a more advanced implementation.\\n\\n    return follow_up_questions\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    candidate_response1 = \\\"I worked on a project where we used a dynamic programming approach to solve a complex optimization problem. We faced some challenges with memory management.\\\"\\n    previous_question1 = \\\"Tell me about a challenging project you worked on.\\\"\\n    topic1 = \\\"Project Experience\\\"\\n    follow_up_questions1 = generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response1, previous_question1, topic1)\\n    print(f\\\"Follow-up questions for response 1: {follow_up_questions1}\\\")\\n\\n    candidate_response2 = \\\"I had a conflict with a team member. I addressed it by communicating directly and finding a compromise.\\\"\\n    previous_question2 = \\\"Tell me about a time you had a conflict with a colleague.\\\"\\n    topic2 = \\\"Behavioral - Conflict Resolution\\\"\\n    follow_up_questions2 = generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response2, previous_question2, topic2, depth=2)\\n    print(f\\\"Follow-up questions for response 2 (depth=2): {follow_up_questions2}\\\")\\n\\n    candidate_response3 = \\\"I have experience with different sorting algorithms. Merge sort is often a good choice.\\\"\\n    previous_question3 = \\\"What sorting algorithms are you familiar with?\\\"\\n    topic3 = \\\"Algorithms\\\"\\n    follow_up_questions3 = generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response3, previous_question3, topic3, depth=1)\\n    print(f\\\"Follow-up questions for response 3: {follow_up_questions3}\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:37.017558\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:40,808", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Implement a resume and job-description analysis module that extracts skills, experiences, and performs a match score.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeJobAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description, resume):\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.resume = resume\\n        self.job_keywords = self.extract_keywords(job_description)\\n        self.resume_keywords = self.extract_keywords(resume)\\n\\n    def extract_keywords(self, text):\\n        # Convert to lowercase and remove special characters\\n        text = text.lower()\\n        text = re.sub(r'[^\\\\w\\\\s]', '', text)\\n\\n        # Split into words and remove common stop words\\n        stop_words = set(['and', 'the', 'a', 'an', 'in', 'on', 'is', 'it', 'to', 'of', 'for', 'with', 'are', 'as', 'at', 'by', 'from'])  # Expand stop words as needed\\n        words = [word for word in text.split() if word not in stop_words]\\n        return words\\n\\n    def calculate_match_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculates a match score based on keyword overlap and experience.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        job_set = set(self.job_keywords)\\n        resume_set = set(self.resume_keywords)\\n\\n        # Keyword matching\\n        keyword_match_count = len(job_set.intersection(resume_set))\\n        keyword_match_percentage = (keyword_match_count / len(job_set)) * 100 if len(job_set) > 0 else 0\\n        keyword_match_percentage = round(keyword_match_percentage, 2)\\n      \\n        # Experience matching (Placeholder - requires more sophisticated parsing)\\n        experience_score = self.analyze_experience()  # Out of 100\\n        \\n        # Combined score - adjust weights as needed\\n        overall_match_score = (0.7 * keyword_match_percentage + 0.3 * experience_score)\\n        \\n        return overall_match_score\\n\\n    def analyze_experience(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Analyzes the experience section for relevant keywords and duration. Returns score out of 100\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        experience_score = 0\\n        \\n        # Placeholder implementation - Enhance with NLP techniques for better accuracy\\n        # Look for keywords related to years of experience, project types, roles mentioned in job description\\n        \\n        years_of_experience = self.extract_experience_years()\\n        \\n        if years_of_experience >= 5:\\n            experience_score = 80\\n        elif years_of_experience >= 3:\\n            experience_score = 60\\n        elif years_of_experience >= 1:\\n            experience_score = 40\\n        else:\\n            experience_score = 20\\n\\n        return experience_score\\n        \\n    def extract_experience_years(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts the number of years of experience from the resume.  Return 0 if nothing found.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        years = 0\\n        # Simple regex to find \\\"X years\\\" or \\\"X+ years\\\"\\n        match = re.search(r'(\\\\d+)\\\\+?\\\\syears', self.resume.lower())\\n        if match:\\n            try:\\n              years = int(match.group(1))\\n            except:\\n              years = 0\\n        return years\\n\\n    def get_resume_summary(self):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"Returns a summary of the resume analysis.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         return f\\\"Keyword match percentage: {round(self.calculate_match_score(), 2)}%\\\"\\n\\n\\n    def run_analysis(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Runs the analysis and returns the results.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        match_score = self.calculate_match_score()\\n        resume_summary = self.get_resume_summary()\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"match_score\\\": match_score,\\n            \\\"resume_summary\\\": resume_summary,\\n            \\\"job_keywords\\\": self.job_keywords,\\n            \\\"resume_keywords\\\": self.resume_keywords\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_description = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Software Engineer - Python\\n    We are looking for a skilled software engineer with 5+ years of experience in Python development.\\n    Experience with Django, REST APIs, and database design is required.\\n    Must have experience with Agile development methodologies.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    resume = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    Software Engineer\\n\\n    Summary:\\n    Experienced software engineer with 7 years of experience in Python.\\n\\n    Skills:\\n    Python, Django, REST APIs, SQL, Agile\\n\\n    Experience:\\n    Software Engineer at ABC Company (2016-Present)\\n    - Developed and maintained REST APIs using Django\\n    - Designed and implemented database schemas\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    analyzer = ResumeJobAnalyzer(job_description, resume)\\n    analysis_result = analyzer.run_analysis()\\n\\n    print(f\\\"Match Score: {analysis_result['match_score']:.2f}%\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Resume Summary: {analysis_result['resume_summary']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Job Keywords: {analysis_result['job_keywords']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Resume Keywords: {analysis_result['resume_keywords']}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Develop an interview question generator for technical and behavioral topics based on the role requirements.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop a recruiter email generator for sending interview invitations and follow-up messages.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\\n\\nclass EmailGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password):\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\\n        self.sender_password = sender_password\\n\\n    def create_invitation_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, interview_date, interview_time, interviewer_name, interview_details):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates an interview invitation email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are pleased to invite you to an interview for the {role_name} position at [Company Name].\\n\\nDate: {interview_date}\\nTime: {interview_time}\\nInterviewer: {interviewer_name}\\nDetails: {interview_details}\\n\\nPlease confirm your availability by replying to this email.\\n\\nWe look forward to speaking with you.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_followup_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, interviewer_name, role_name):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates a follow-up email after the interview.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Following Up on Your Interview for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to interview for the {role_name} position at [Company Name] with {interviewer_name}.\\n\\nWe appreciate you sharing your experience and qualifications with us. We are currently reviewing all candidates and will be in touch soon regarding the next steps.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_rejection_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates a rejection email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Update on Your Application for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for your interest in the {role_name} position at [Company Name]. We appreciate you taking the time to apply.\\n\\nWe have carefully reviewed your application and have decided to move forward with other candidates whose qualifications and experience are a closer match for the requirements of this role.\\n\\nWe wish you the best in your job search.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_offer_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, salary, start_date):\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates an offer email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      subject = f\\\"Job Offer: {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n      body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are delighted to offer you the position of {role_name} at [Company Name]!\\n\\nWe were very impressed with your qualifications and experience during the interview process.\\n\\nHere are the details of the offer:\\n\\n* Role: {role_name}\\n* Salary: {salary}\\n* Start Date: {start_date}\\n\\nA formal offer letter with more details will follow shortly. Please let us know if you have any questions.\\n\\nWe are excited about the possibility of you joining our team!\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Creates and returns a MIMEText email object.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = MIMEText(body)\\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\\n        return msg\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Sends an email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n        try:\\n            with smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port) as server:\\n                server.starttls()\\n                server.login(self.sender_email, self.sender_password)\\n                server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipient_email, msg.as_string())\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent to {recipient_email}\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error sending email: {e}\\\")\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    smtp_server = 'smtp.gmail.com'  # Replace with your SMTP server\\n    smtp_port = 587  # Replace with your SMTP port\\n    sender_email = 'your_email@gmail.com'  # Replace with your email\\n    sender_password = 'your_password'  # Replace with your password (or app password)\\n\\n    email_generator = EmailGenerator(smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password)\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an interview invitation\\n    recipient_email = 'candidate@example.com'\\n    candidate_name = 'Jane Smith'\\n    role_name = 'Software Engineer'\\n    interview_date = datetime.now() + timedelta(days=2)\\n    interview_date_str = interview_date.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d\\\")\\n    interview_time = \\\"10:00 AM\\\"\\n    interviewer_name = 'John Doe'\\n    interview_details = \\\"Please join the Zoom meeting: [Zoom Link]\\\"\\n\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Interview Invitation for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_invitation_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, interview_date_str, interview_time, interviewer_name, interview_details).get_payload()) #Fixed: Correctly pass recipient email, subject, and body\\n\\n    # Example: Sending a follow-up email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Following Up on Your Interview for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_followup_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, interviewer_name, role_name).get_payload())\\n    \\n    # Example: Sending a rejection email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Update on Your Application for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_rejection_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name).get_payload())\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an offer email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Job Offer: {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_offer_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, \\\"$120,000\\\", \\\"2024-08-01\\\").get_payload())\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:40.808785\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:42,649", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Implement a report generator that compiles resume-job match, interview summary, technical & behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and final recommendations into a .txt file.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement an evaluation engine that scores candidate answers on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy across categories.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass EvaluationEngine:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates candidate answers based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, scoring_weights=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EvaluationEngine with optional scoring weights.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            scoring_weights (dict, optional): A dictionary specifying the weights for each evaluation criterion.\\n                                             Defaults to equal weights if None.  Example: {'relevance': 0.3, 'depth': 0.3, 'confidence': 0.2, 'accuracy': 0.2}\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if scoring_weights is None:\\n            self.scoring_weights = {'relevance': 0.25, 'depth': 0.25, 'confidence': 0.25, 'accuracy': 0.25}\\n        else:\\n            self.scoring_weights = scoring_weights\\n\\n        self.validate_scoring_weights()\\n\\n    def validate_scoring_weights(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Validates that the scoring weights sum up to 1.\\n        Raises a ValueError if the weights are invalid.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_weight = sum(self.scoring_weights.values())\\n        if not abs(total_weight - 1.0) < 1e-6:  # Using a small tolerance for floating-point comparison\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Scoring weights must sum up to 1.0\\\")\\n\\n    def score_answer(self, answer, expected_answer, question_type=\\\"technical\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Scores a candidate's answer based on several criteria.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            expected_answer (str): The ideal answer or a rubric for scoring.\\n            question_type (str): The type of question (\\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\").  Affects the scoring criteria.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing the scores for each criterion and the overall score.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n        relevance_score = self.evaluate_relevance(answer, expected_answer)\\n        depth_score = self.evaluate_depth(answer, expected_answer, question_type)\\n        confidence_score = self.evaluate_confidence(answer)\\n        accuracy_score = self.evaluate_accuracy(answer, expected_answer, question_type)\\n\\n        overall_score = (\\n            self.scoring_weights['relevance'] * relevance_score +\\n            self.scoring_weights['depth'] * depth_score +\\n            self.scoring_weights['confidence'] * confidence_score +\\n            self.scoring_weights['accuracy'] * accuracy_score\\n        )\\n\\n        return {\\n            'relevance': relevance_score,\\n            'depth': depth_score,\\n            'confidence': confidence_score,\\n            'accuracy': accuracy_score,\\n            'overall': overall_score\\n        }\\n\\n    def evaluate_relevance(self, answer, expected_answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the relevance of the answer to the question.\\n        This is a placeholder and should be improved with NLP techniques.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            expected_answer (str): The ideal answer or a rubric for scoring.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: A score between 0 and 1 representing the relevance.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Simple keyword matching as a starting point\\n        expected_keywords = set(expected_answer.lower().split())\\n        answer_keywords = set(answer.lower().split())\\n        common_keywords = expected_keywords.intersection(answer_keywords)\\n\\n        relevance_score = len(common_keywords) / max(len(expected_keywords), 1)  # Avoid division by zero\\n\\n        return min(relevance_score, 1.0) # Ensure score is within 0-1 range\\n\\n    def evaluate_depth(self, answer, expected_answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the depth of the answer.\\n        This is a placeholder and should be improved with more sophisticated analysis.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            expected_answer (str): The ideal answer or a rubric for scoring.\\n            question_type (str): The type of question (\\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\").\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: A score between 0 and 1 representing the depth.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n        answer_length = len(answer.split())\\n        expected_length = len(expected_answer.split()) # rough estimate of expected answer length\\n\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n             depth_score = min(answer_length / max(expected_length,10) , 1.0)  # Scale by a factor\\n\\n        elif question_type == \\\"behavioral\\\":\\n            depth_score = min(answer_length / max(expected_length, 20), 1.0) # Behavioral answers often require more context\\n        else:\\n            depth_score = 0.5 # default if question type is unrecognized\\n\\n        return depth_score\\n\\n    def evaluate_confidence(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the confidence level expressed in the answer.\\n        This is a placeholder and could be improved with sentiment analysis or tone detection.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: A score between 0 and 1 representing the confidence.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Simple check for hedging language\\n        hedging_words = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"I believe\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"perhaps\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\", \\\"I guess\\\"]\\n        hedging_count = sum([1 for word in hedging_words if word in answer.lower()])\\n        confidence_score = 1.0 - min(hedging_count * 0.2, 1.0)  # Penalize for each hedging word\\n\\n        return confidence_score\\n\\n    def evaluate_accuracy(self, answer, expected_answer, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the technical accuracy of the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            expected_answer (str): The ideal answer or a rubric for scoring.\\n            question_type (str): The type of question.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: A score between 0 and 1 representing the accuracy.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            # This is a simplified example.  Ideally, you would parse the answer and compare it against known facts.\\n            expected_keywords = set(expected_answer.lower().split())\\n            answer_keywords = set(answer.lower().split())\\n            correct_keywords = expected_keywords.intersection(answer_keywords)\\n            accuracy_score = len(correct_keywords) / max(len(expected_keywords), 1)\\n        else:\\n            # For behavioral questions, accuracy is less relevant, so assign a default value.\\n            accuracy_score = 0.8  # Assume generally truthful\\n\\n        return min(accuracy_score, 1.0)  # Ensure score is within the valid range\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    engine = EvaluationEngine()\\n\\n    # Technical Question Example\\n    technical_question = \\\"What is the difference between a stack and a queue?\\\"\\n    candidate_answer_technical = \\\"A stack is LIFO and a queue is FIFO.\\\"\\n    expected_answer_technical = \\\"Stack: LIFO (Last In, First Out). Queue: FIFO (First In, First Out).\\\"\\n    technical_scores = engine.score_answer(candidate_answer_technical, expected_answer_technical, question_type=\\\"technical\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Technical Question Scores:\\\", technical_scores)\\n\\n    # Behavioral Question Example\\n    behavioral_question = \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\"\\n    candidate_answer_behavioral = \\\"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the workload. I learned to plan better.\\\"\\n    expected_answer_behavioral = \\\"Situation: Briefly describe the situation. Task: What was your responsibility? Action: What steps did you take? Result: What was the outcome? What did you learn?\\\"\\n    behavioral_scores = engine.score_answer(candidate_answer_behavioral, expected_answer_behavioral, question_type=\\\"behavioral\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Behavioral Question Scores:\\\", behavioral_scores)\\n\\n    # Example with custom weights\\n    custom_engine = EvaluationEngine(scoring_weights={'relevance': 0.4, 'depth': 0.3, 'confidence': 0.1, 'accuracy': 0.2})\\n    technical_scores_custom = custom_engine.score_answer(candidate_answer_technical, expected_answer_technical, question_type=\\\"technical\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Technical Question Scores with Custom Weights:\\\", technical_scores_custom)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:42.649530\"\n}"}
