{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:46,644", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:46.644774\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Build a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\", \"result\": \"```python\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_question, topic, depth=1):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\\n        previous_question (str): The question that elicited the response.\\n        topic (str): The general topic of the interview question.\\n        depth (int):  The desired depth/specificity of the follow-up question. Higher depth ...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current implementation is very simplistic and relies solely on hard-coded keyword checks in `topic` and `candidate_response`.  \\n2. It ignores the `previous_question` completely, which could be used to reference context or tailor the phrasing of the follow‐up.  \\n3. There are only two depth levels; adding more depths and richer templates would improve the dynamism.  \\n4. It doesn’t leverage even basic NLP (e.g., extracting key nouns/metrics) to generate more targeted questions.  \\n5. The fallback questions are too generic.  \\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, previous_question, topic, depth=1):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\\n        previous_question (str): The question that elicited the response.\\n        topic (str): The general topic of the interview question.\\n        depth (int): Desired specificity: \\n                     1 = clarifying detail, \\n                     2 = probing reasoning/metrics, \\n                     3 = exploring broader implications/alternatives.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: Follow-up questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    response = candidate_response.strip().lower()\\n    questions = []\\n\\n    # Helper to capitalize first letter\\n    def cap(q): \\n        return q[0].upper() + q[1:]\\n\\n    # Depth 1: Clarify or request specifics\\n    if depth >= 1:\\n        # If candidate mentions a project or experience\\n        if re.search(r'\\\\b(project|experience|worked|led)\\\\b', response) or 'project' in topic.lower():\\n            questions.append(\\\"Can you walk me through the main steps you took in that project?\\\")\\n        # If candidate mentions an algorithm or data structure\\n        if re.search(r'\\\\b(algorithm|data structure|dp|sorting|tree|graph)\\\\b', response) or 'algorithm' in topic.lower():\\n            questions.append(\\\"Which part of that algorithm/data structure was most challenging to implement?\\\")\\n        # If the question was behavioral/conflict related\\n        if 'behavioral' in topic.lower() or 'conflict' in topic.lower():\\n            questions.append(\\\"What was the immediate impact on the team dynamic?\\\")\\n        # Generic clarifier\\n        questions.append(\\\"Could you elaborate on that point a bit more?\\\")\\n\\n    # Depth 2: Probe reasoning, trade-offs, metrics\\n    if depth >= 2:\\n        # Detect mention of complexity or performance\\n        if 'time complexity' in response or 'space complexity' in response or 'performance' in response:\\n            questions.append(\\\"How did you measure or benchmark that performance in practice?\\\")\\n        # Detect mention of challenges/obstacles\\n        if re.search(r'\\\\b(challenge|issue|problem)\\\\b', response):\\n            questions.append(\\\"What alternative approaches did you consider before settling on your solution?\\\")\\n        # Detect mention of learning or reflection\\n        if re.search(r'\\\\b(learned|improved|reflected)\\\\b', response):\\n            questions.append(\\\"How have you applied that learning in subsequent roles or projects?\\\")\\n        # Generic deeper probe\\n        questions.append(\\\"What would you do differently if you tackled this again?\\\")\\n\\n    # Depth 3: Explore broader context, impact, and hypothetical variations\\n    if depth >= 3:\\n        questions.append(\\\"How would you handle this scenario if the scale doubled/tripled?\\\")\\n        questions.append(\\\"Can you describe how you collaborated with cross-functional stakeholders on this?\\\")\\n        questions.append(\\\"What lessons from this experience could you transfer to a different domain or technology?\\\")\\n\\n    # Ensure uniqueness and reasonable ordering\\n    unique_questions = []\\n    for q in questions:\\n        q = cap(q.rstrip('?')) + '?'\\n        if q not in unique_questions:\\n            unique_questions.append(q)\\n\\n    # Optionally reference the previous question context in the first prompt\\n    if unique_questions:\\n        unique_questions[0] = f\\\"Regarding your answer to \\\\\\\"{previous_question}\\\\\\\", {unique_questions[0]}\\\"\\n\\n    return unique_questions\\n\\n\\n# Example Usage\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    resp1 = (\\\"I worked on a project where we used a dynamic programming \\\"\\n             \\\"approach to solve a complex optimization problem. We faced \\\"\\n             \\\"some challenges with memory management and performance tuning.\\\")\\n    prev_q1 = \\\"Tell me about a challenging project you worked on.\\\"\\n    topic1 = \\\"Project Experience\\\"\\n    print(generate_follow_up_questions(resp1, prev_q1, topic1, depth=2))\\n\\n    resp2 = (\\\"I had a conflict with a team member. I addressed it by \\\"\\n             \\\"communicating directly and finding a compromise.\\\")\\n    prev_q2 = \\\"Describe a time you had a conflict with a colleague.\\\"\\n    topic2 = \\\"Behavioral - Conflict Resolution\\\"\\n    print(generate_follow_up_questions(resp2, prev_q2, topic2, depth=3))\\n```\\n\\nExplanation of improvements:\\n- Uses `previous_question` in the first follow-up for clear context.\\n- Multiple depth levels with richer templates.\\n- Regex checks on `candidate_response` to dynamically trigger relevant probes.\\n- Ensures unique, well-formatted questions.\\n- Generic and topic-specific branches for greater coverage.\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:21:58,730", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Implement a resume and job-description analysis module that extracts skills, experiences, and performs a match score.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass ResumeJobAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description, resume):\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.resume = resume\\n        self.job_keywords = self.extract_keywords(job_description)\\n        self.resume_keywords = self.extract_keywords(resume)\\n\\n    def extract_keywords(self, text):\\n        # Convert to lowercase and remove special characters\\n        text = text.lower()\\n        text = re.sub(r'[^\\\\w\\\\s]', '', text)\\n\\n        # Split into words and remove common stop words\\n        stop_words = set(['and', 'the', 'a', 'an', 'in', 'on', 'is', 'it', 'to', 'of', 'for', 'with', 'are', 'as', 'at', 'by', 'from'])  # Expand stop words as needed\\n        words = [word for word in text.split() if word not in stop_words]\\n        return words\\n\\n    def calculate_match_score(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculates a match score based on keyword overlap and experience.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        job_set = set(self.job_keywords)\\n        resume_set = set(self.resume_keywords)\\n\\n        # Keyword matching\\n        keyword_match_count = len(job_set.intersection(resume_set))\\n        keyword_match_percentage = (keyword_match_count / len(job_set)) * 100 if len(job_set) > 0 else 0\\n        keyword_match_percentage = round(keyword_match_percentage, 2)\\n      \\n        # Experience matching (Placeholder - requires more sophisticated parsing)\\n        experience_score = self.analyze_experience()  # Out of 100\\n        \\n        # Combined score - adjust weights as needed\\n        overall_match_score = (0.7 * keyword_match_percentage + 0.3 * experience_score)\\n        \\n        return overall_match_score\\n\\n    def analyze_experience(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Analyzes the experience section for relevant keywords and duration. Returns score out of 100\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        experience_score = 0\\n        \\n        # Placeholder implementation - Enhance with NLP techniques for better accuracy\\n        # Look for keywords related to years of experience, project types, roles mentioned in job description\\n        \\n        years_of_experience = self.extract_experience_years()\\n        \\n        if years_of_experience >= 5:\\n            experience_score = 80\\n        elif years_of_experience >= 3:\\n            experience_score = 60\\n        elif years_of_experience >= 1:\\n            experience_score = 40\\n        else:\\n            experience_score = 20\\n\\n        return experience_score\\n        \\n    def extract_experience_years(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Extracts the number of years of experience from the resume.  Return 0 if nothing found.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        years = 0\\n        # Simple regex to find \\\"X years\\\" or \\\"X+ years\\\"\\n        match = re.search(r'(\\\\d+)\\\\+?\\\\syears', self.resume.lower())\\n        if match:\\n            try:\\n              years = int(match.group(1))\\n            except:\\n              years = 0\\n        return years\\n\\n    def get_resume_summary(self):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"Returns a summary of the resume analysis.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         return f\\\"Keyword match percentage: {round(self.calculate_match_score(), 2)}%\\\"\\n\\n\\n    def run_analysis(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Runs the analysis and returns the results.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        match_score = self.calculate_match_score()\\n        resume_summary = self.get_resume_summary()\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"match_score\\\": match_score,\\n            \\\"resume_summary\\\": resume_summary,\\n            \\\"job_keywords\\\": self.job_keywords,\\n            \\\"resume_keywords\\\": self.resume_keywords\\n        }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    job_description = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Software Engineer - Python\\n    We are looking for a skilled software engineer with 5+ years of experience in Python development.\\n    Experience with Django, REST APIs, and database design is required.\\n    Must have experience with Agile development methodologies.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    resume = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    Software Engineer\\n\\n    Summary:\\n    Experienced software engineer with 7 years of experience in Python.\\n\\n    Skills:\\n    Python, Django, REST APIs, SQL, Agile\\n\\n    Experience:\\n    Software Engineer at ABC Company (2016-Present)\\n    - Developed and maintained REST APIs using Django\\n    - Designed and implemented database schemas\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    analyzer = ResumeJobAnalyzer(job_description, resume)\\n    analysis_result = analyzer.run_analysis()\\n\\n    print(f\\\"Match Score: {analysis_result['match_score']:.2f}%\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Resume Summary: {analysis_result['resume_summary']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Job Keywords: {analysis_result['job_keywords']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Resume Keywords: {analysis_result['resume_keywords']}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement a report generator that compiles resume-job match, interview summary, technical & behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and final recommendations into a .txt file.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text (.txt)\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass ReportGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, analysis_result, interview_summary, technical_assessment, behavioral_assessment, strengths, weaknesses, final_recommendation, candidate_name=\\\"Candidate\\\"):\\n        self.analysis_result = analysis_result\\n        self.interview_summary = interview_summary\\n        self.technical_assessment = technical_assessment\\n        self.behavioral_assessment = behavioral_assessment\\n        self.strengths = strengths\\n        self.weaknesses = weaknesses\\n        self.final_recommendation = final_recommendation\\n        self.candidate_name = candidate_name\\n\\n    def generate_report(self, filename=\\\"candidate_evaluation_report.txt\\\"):\\n        with open(filename, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n            f.write(f\\\"Candidate Evaluation Report: {self.candidate_name}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"=========================================\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"I. Resume-Job Match Analysis\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Match Score: {self.analysis_result['match_score']:.2f}%\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Resume Summary: {self.analysis_result['resume_summary']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Job Keywords: {', '.join(self.analysis_result['job_keywords'])}\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"Resume Keywords: {', '.join(self.analysis_result['resume_keywords'])}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"II. Interview Summary\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.interview_summary}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"III. Technical Assessment\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.technical_assessment}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"IV. Behavioral Assessment\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.behavioral_assessment}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"V. Strengths\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.strengths}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"VI. Weaknesses\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.weaknesses}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n            f.write(\\\"VII. Final Recommendation and Scoring Breakdown\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(\\\"-----------------------------------------\\\\n\\\")\\n            f.write(f\\\"{self.final_recommendation}\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n        return filename  # Return the filename of the generated report\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (mock data)\\n    analysis_result = {\\n        \\\"match_score\\\": 85.5,\\n        \\\"resume_summary\\\": \\\"Strong match based on keywords and experience.\\\",\\n        \\\"job_keywords\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"django\\\", \\\"rest api\\\", \\\"database\\\", \\\"agile\\\"],\\n        \\\"resume_keywords\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"django\\\", \\\"rest api\\\", \\\"sql\\\", \\\"agile\\\"]\\n    }\\n\\n    interview_summary = \\\"Candidate demonstrated good communication skills and a solid understanding of software development principles. Showed enthusiasm for the role.\\\"\\n    technical_assessment = \\\"Candidate answered technical questions accurately, demonstrating a strong understanding of Python and Django. Performance on coding exercise was satisfactory.\\\"\\n    behavioral_assessment = \\\"Candidate provided thoughtful responses to behavioral questions, highlighting teamwork and problem-solving skills.\\\"\\n    strengths = \\\"Strong technical skills in Python/Django, good communication, team player.\\\"\\n    weaknesses = \\\"Could improve on experience with large-scale systems. Lacks experience with specific cloud technologies.\\\"\\n    final_recommendation = \\\"Recommend hiring. Overall score: 8.7/10. Strong technical foundation and good cultural fit.\\\"\\n\\n    report_generator = ReportGenerator(analysis_result, interview_summary, technical_assessment, behavioral_assessment, strengths, weaknesses, final_recommendation, candidate_name=\\\"John Doe\\\")\\n    report_file = report_generator.generate_report()\\n    print(f\\\"Report generated: {report_file}\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:21:58.730558\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:22:00,680", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Develop a recruiter email generator for sending interview invitations and follow-up messages.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\\n\\nclass EmailGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password):\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\\n        self.sender_password = sender_password\\n\\n    def create_invitation_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, interview_date, interview_time, interviewer_name, interview_details):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates an interview invitation email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are pleased to invite you to an interview for the {role_name} position at [Company Name].\\n\\nDate: {interview_date}\\nTime: {interview_time}\\nInterviewer: {interviewer_name}\\nDetails: {interview_details}\\n\\nPlease confirm your availability by replying to this email.\\n\\nWe look forward to speaking with you.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_followup_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, interviewer_name, role_name):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates a follow-up email after the interview.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Following Up on Your Interview for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to interview for the {role_name} position at [Company Name] with {interviewer_name}.\\n\\nWe appreciate you sharing your experience and qualifications with us. We are currently reviewing all candidates and will be in touch soon regarding the next steps.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_rejection_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates a rejection email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Update on Your Application for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for your interest in the {role_name} position at [Company Name]. We appreciate you taking the time to apply.\\n\\nWe have carefully reviewed your application and have decided to move forward with other candidates whose qualifications and experience are a closer match for the requirements of this role.\\n\\nWe wish you the best in your job search.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_offer_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, salary, start_date):\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"Generates an offer email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      subject = f\\\"Job Offer: {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\"\\n      body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are delighted to offer you the position of {role_name} at [Company Name]!\\n\\nWe were very impressed with your qualifications and experience during the interview process.\\n\\nHere are the details of the offer:\\n\\n* Role: {role_name}\\n* Salary: {salary}\\n* Start Date: {start_date}\\n\\nA formal offer letter with more details will follow shortly. Please let us know if you have any questions.\\n\\nWe are excited about the possibility of you joining our team!\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\n[Your Title]\\n[Company Name]\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      return self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def create_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Creates and returns a MIMEText email object.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = MIMEText(body)\\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\\n        return msg\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Sends an email.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = self.create_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n        try:\\n            with smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port) as server:\\n                server.starttls()\\n                server.login(self.sender_email, self.sender_password)\\n                server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipient_email, msg.as_string())\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent to {recipient_email}\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error sending email: {e}\\\")\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    smtp_server = 'smtp.gmail.com'  # Replace with your SMTP server\\n    smtp_port = 587  # Replace with your SMTP port\\n    sender_email = 'your_email@gmail.com'  # Replace with your email\\n    sender_password = 'your_password'  # Replace with your password (or app password)\\n\\n    email_generator = EmailGenerator(smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password)\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an interview invitation\\n    recipient_email = 'candidate@example.com'\\n    candidate_name = 'Jane Smith'\\n    role_name = 'Software Engineer'\\n    interview_date = datetime.now() + timedelta(days=2)\\n    interview_date_str = interview_date.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d\\\")\\n    interview_time = \\\"10:00 AM\\\"\\n    interviewer_name = 'John Doe'\\n    interview_details = \\\"Please join the Zoom meeting: [Zoom Link]\\\"\\n\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Interview Invitation for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_invitation_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, interview_date_str, interview_time, interviewer_name, interview_details).get_payload()) #Fixed: Correctly pass recipient email, subject, and body\\n\\n    # Example: Sending a follow-up email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Following Up on Your Interview for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_followup_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, interviewer_name, role_name).get_payload())\\n    \\n    # Example: Sending a rejection email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Update on Your Application for {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_rejection_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name).get_payload())\\n\\n    # Example: Sending an offer email\\n    email_generator.send_email(recipient_email,\\n                               f\\\"Job Offer: {role_name} at [Company Name]\\\",\\n                               email_generator.create_offer_email(recipient_email, candidate_name, role_name, \\\"$120,000\\\", \\\"2024-08-01\\\").get_payload())\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Build a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop an interview question generator for technical and behavioral topics based on the role requirements.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass InterviewQuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, role_requirements):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewQuestionGenerator with the role requirements.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            role_requirements (str): A description of the role requirements.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.role_requirements = role_requirements\\n\\n    def generate_technical_questions(self, job_description):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates technical interview questions based on the job description.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description (str): The job description for the role.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            list: A list of technical interview questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        technical_questions = []\\n\\n        # Extract technical skills from job description\\n        skills = self.extract_skills(job_description)\\n\\n        # Generate questions based on the extracted skills\\n        for skill in skills:\\n            technical_questions.append(f\\\"Explain your experience with {skill}.\\\")\\n            technical_questions.append(f\\\"Describe a project where you used {skill}.\\\")\\n            technical_questions.append(f\\\"What are the advantages and disadvantages of using {skill}?\\\")\\n            technical_questions.append(f\\\"How do you troubleshoot issues related to {skill}?\\\")\\n\\n        # Add some general technical questions\\n        technical_questions.append(\\\"Describe your experience with software development methodologies (e.g., Agile, Waterfall).\\\")\\n        technical_questions.append(\\\"Explain the difference between a stack and a queue.\\\")\\n        technical_questions.append(\\\"What is the purpose of version control systems like Git?\\\")\\n        technical_questions.append(\\\"How do you approach debugging a complex software issue?\\\")\\n        technical_questions.append(\\\"Explain the concept of object-oriented programming.\\\")\\n\\n        return technical_questions\\n\\n    def generate_behavioral_questions(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates behavioral interview questions based on the role requirements.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            list: A list of behavioral interview questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        behavioral_questions = []\\n\\n        # Generate questions based on common behavioral competencies\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Tell me about a time you had to work under pressure. How did you handle it?\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Describe a situation where you had to deal with a difficult colleague. How did you resolve the conflict?\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Give an example of a time you failed. What did you learn from it?\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Tell me about a time you had to make a quick decision with limited information.\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Describe a situation where you had to lead a team to achieve a common goal.\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"How do you handle receiving negative feedback?\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Tell me about a time you went above and beyond what was expected of you.\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Describe your approach to problem-solving.\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"How do you stay motivated and productive when facing challenging tasks?\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Explain how you prioritize tasks when faced with multiple deadlines.\\\")\\n        behavioral_questions.append(\\\"Describe a time when you had to adapt to a significant change in the workplace.\\\")\\n\\n        return behavioral_questions\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self, job_description):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts technical skills from the job description.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            list: A list of extracted skills.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # This is a placeholder.  A more sophisticated implementation would use NLP techniques.\\n        # For now, let's just return some hardcoded skills based on common keywords.\\n        skills = []\\n        job_description = job_description.lower()\\n        if \\\"python\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Python\\\")\\n        if \\\"java\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Java\\\")\\n        if \\\"c++\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"C++\\\")\\n        if \\\"javascript\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"JavaScript\\\")\\n        if \\\"sql\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"SQL\\\")\\n        if \\\"aws\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"AWS\\\")\\n        if \\\"azure\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Azure\\\")\\n        if \\\"docker\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Docker\\\")\\n        if \\\"kubernetes\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Kubernetes\\\")\\n        if \\\"machine learning\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Machine Learning\\\")\\n        if \\\"data science\\\" in job_description:\\n            skills.append(\\\"Data Science\\\")\\n        return skills\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    role_requirements = \\\"Software Engineer with experience in Python and AWS.\\\"\\n    job_description = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    We are looking for a Software Engineer to join our team.\\n    The ideal candidate should have experience with Python, AWS, and SQL.\\n    Experience with Docker and Kubernetes is a plus.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    question_generator = InterviewQuestionGenerator(role_requirements)\\n\\n    technical_questions = question_generator.generate_technical_questions(job_description)\\n    print(\\\"Technical Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in technical_questions:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n\\n    behavioral_questions = question_generator.generate_behavioral_questions()\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in behavioral_questions:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:22:00.679971\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:22:00,813", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement an evaluation engine that scores candidate answers on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy across categories.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, job_description, previous_questions=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response, considering the job description and previous questions asked.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response to the previous question.\\n        job_description (str): The job description for the role.\\n        previous_questions (list, optional): A list of previously asked questions. Defaults to None.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of follow-up questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    follow_up_questions = []\\n\\n    # 1. Analyze the candidate's response for keywords and areas of interest/expertise\\n    keywords = extract_keywords(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # 2. Identify areas where the candidate was vague or lacked depth\\n    areas_for_clarification = identify_areas_for_clarification(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # 3. Check for alignment with the job description's requirements\\n    missing_skills = identify_missing_skills(keywords, job_description)\\n\\n    # 4. Generate follow-up questions based on the above analysis\\n    if keywords:\\n        follow_up_questions.extend([\\n            f\\\"Could you elaborate on your experience with {keyword}?\\\",\\n            f\\\"How have you used {keyword} in a professional setting?\\\",\\n        for keyword in keywords])\\n\\n    if areas_for_clarification:\\n        follow_up_questions.extend([\\n            f\\\"Could you provide more details about {area}?\\\",\\n            f\\\"What were the specific challenges you faced when dealing with {area}?\\\",\\n        for area in areas_for_clarification])\\n\\n    if missing_skills:\\n        follow_up_questions.extend([\\n            f\\\"How familiar are you with {skill}?\\\",\\n            f\\\"Have you had any exposure to {skill} in your previous roles or personal projects?\\\",\\n        for skill in missing_skills])\\n\\n    # 5. Avoid redundant questions (if previous questions are provided)\\n    if previous_questions:\\n        follow_up_questions = [q for q in follow_up_questions if q not in previous_questions]\\n\\n    return follow_up_questions\\n\\ndef extract_keywords(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts keywords from a given text.\\n    This is a placeholder and can be improved with NLP techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to extract keywords from.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of keywords.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple keyword extraction based on word frequency and excluding common stop words\\n    stop_words = set([\\\"the\\\", \\\"a\\\", \\\"an\\\", \\\"in\\\", \\\"on\\\", \\\"is\\\", \\\"it\\\", \\\"to\\\", \\\"of\\\", \\\"and\\\", \\\"for\\\", \\\"with\\\", \\\"I\\\", \\\"my\\\", \\\"me\\\"])\\n    words = re.findall(r'\\\\b\\\\w+\\\\b', text.lower())\\n    word_counts = {}\\n    for word in words:\\n        if word not in stop_words:\\n            word_counts[word] = word_counts.get(word, 0) + 1\\n\\n    # Return the 3 most frequent words as keywords\\n    sorted_words = sorted(word_counts.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\\n    return [word for word, count in sorted_words[:3]]\\n\\ndef identify_areas_for_clarification(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies areas in the text that require further clarification.\\n    This is a placeholder and can be improved with NLP techniques.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        text (str): The text to analyze.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of areas for clarification.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple identification based on phrases like \\\"I think\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"it depends\\\"\\n    clarification_areas = []\\n    if \\\"I think\\\" in text.lower():\\n        clarification_areas.append(\\\"the reasoning behind their thinking\\\")\\n    if \\\"maybe\\\" in text.lower():\\n        clarification_areas.append(\\\"the possibility under consideration\\\")\\n    if \\\"it depends\\\" in text.lower():\\n        clarification_areas.append(\\\"the conditions that influence the outcome\\\")\\n\\n    return clarification_areas\\n\\ndef identify_missing_skills(keywords, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies skills mentioned in the job description that are not present in the keywords.\\n    This is a placeholder and can be improved with more sophisticated matching.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        keywords (list): A list of keywords extracted from the candidate's response.\\n        job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of missing skills.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple matching of keywords to job description requirements\\n    job_description_keywords = extract_keywords(job_description)\\n    missing_skills = [skill for skill in job_description_keywords if skill not in keywords]\\n    return missing_skills\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage:\\n    job_description = \\\"We are looking for a software engineer with experience in Python, Django, and REST APIs.\\\"\\n    candidate_response = \\\"I have some experience with Python and web development. I have built a few personal projects.\\\"\\n    previous_questions = [\\\"Tell me about your experience with Python?\\\"]\\n\\n    follow_up_questions = generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, job_description, previous_questions)\\n\\n    print(\\\"Follow-up Questions:\\\")\\n    for question in follow_up_questions:\\n        print(f\\\"- {question}\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:22:00.813243\"\n}"}
