{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:22:10,913", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:22:10.913384\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Build a follow-up question generation component that dynamically creates questions based on candidate responses.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, job_description, previous_questions=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response, considering the job description and previous questions asked.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_response (str): The candidate's response to the previous question.\\n        job_description (str): The job description for the role.\\n        previous_questions (list, optional): A list of previously asked questions. De...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The list comprehensions for generating questions are syntactically incorrect. They need to iterate over items to produce questions properly.\\n2. Duplicate and redundant questions should be normalized (e.g., lowercased) and filtered against `previous_questions`.\\n3. The keyword extraction and missing-skills identification can be made clearer and more robust using Python’s `collections.Counter`.\\n4. Provide clearer question templates and loop over each keyword/area/skill.\\n5. Ensure the code is valid Python and includes an example usage.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\nfrom collections import Counter\\n\\ndef generate_follow_up_questions(candidate_response, job_description, previous_questions=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates follow-up questions based on a candidate's response, considering the job description\\n    and any previously asked questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Normalize previous questions for duplicate checking\\n    prev = set(q.strip().lower() for q in (previous_questions or []))\\n\\n    # 1. Extract keywords from candidate response\\n    keywords = extract_keywords(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # 2. Identify vague areas needing clarification\\n    areas = identify_areas_for_clarification(candidate_response)\\n\\n    # 3. Identify missing skills by comparing job description to candidate keywords\\n    missing_skills = identify_missing_skills(keywords, job_description)\\n\\n    # 4. Generate questions\\n    questions = []\\n\\n    for kw in keywords:\\n        questions.append(f\\\"Could you elaborate on your experience with {kw}?\\\")\\n        questions.append(f\\\"How have you applied {kw} in a real-world project?\\\")\\n\\n    for area in areas:\\n        questions.append(f\\\"Can you provide more details about {area}?\\\")\\n        questions.append(f\\\"What challenges did you face when dealing with {area}?\\\")\\n\\n    for skill in missing_skills:\\n        questions.append(f\\\"How familiar are you with {skill}?\\\")\\n        questions.append(f\\\"Have you ever used {skill} in a past role or project?\\\")\\n\\n    # 5. Filter out duplicates and previously asked questions\\n    unique_questions = []\\n    seen = set()\\n    for q in questions:\\n        q_norm = q.strip().lower()\\n        if q_norm not in seen and q_norm not in prev:\\n            seen.add(q_norm)\\n            unique_questions.append(q)\\n\\n    return unique_questions\\n\\n\\ndef extract_keywords(text, top_n=3):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts the top_n most frequent non-stopword tokens from the text.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    stop_words = set([\\n        \\\"the\\\", \\\"a\\\", \\\"an\\\", \\\"in\\\", \\\"on\\\", \\\"is\\\", \\\"it\\\", \\\"to\\\",\\n        \\\"of\\\", \\\"and\\\", \\\"for\\\", \\\"with\\\", \\\"i\\\", \\\"my\\\", \\\"me\\\", \\\"we\\\", \\\"you\\\"\\n    ])\\n    words = re.findall(r'\\\\b\\\\w+\\\\b', text.lower())\\n    filtered = [w for w in words if w not in stop_words and len(w) > 2]\\n    counts = Counter(filtered)\\n    return [word for word, _ in counts.most_common(top_n)]\\n\\n\\ndef identify_areas_for_clarification(text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Identifies vague phrases that may need more detail.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    vagues = {\\n        \\\"i think\\\": \\\"your thought process\\\",\\n        \\\"maybe\\\": \\\"the scenarios you considered\\\",\\n        \\\"it depends\\\": \\\"the conditions influencing your decision\\\"\\n    }\\n    areas = []\\n    low = text.lower()\\n    for phrase, clarification in vagues.items():\\n        if phrase in low:\\n            areas.append(clarification)\\n    return areas\\n\\n\\ndef identify_missing_skills(keywords, job_description, top_n=5):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Finds skills in the job description not covered by the candidate's keywords.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    jd_words = extract_keywords(job_description, top_n=top_n)\\n    return [skill for skill in jd_words if skill not in keywords]\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example usage\\n    job_description = (\\n        \\\"We are seeking a Software Engineer experienced in Python, Django, REST APIs, \\\"\\n        \\\"and cloud deployment (AWS or Azure). Familiarity with Docker and CI/CD pipelines \\\"\\n        \\\"is a plus.\\\"\\n    )\\n    candidate_response = (\\n        \\\"I have solid experience with Python and web development. \\\"\\n        \\\"I think my design choices are driven by scalability needs. \\\"\\n        \\\"I've also done some container work.\\\"\\n    )\\n    previous_questions = [\\n        \\\"Tell me about your experience with Python?\\\"\\n    ]\\n\\n    follow_ups = generate_follow_up_questions(\\n        candidate_response, job_description, previous_questions\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Generated Follow-up Questions:\\\")\\n    for q in follow_ups:\\n        print(f\\\"- {q}\\\")\\n```\"}"}
